english:
  title: Parting from a Friend from Home in Sanyang
  author: Choe Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    We met by chance and briefly savored spring in these distant hills,
    Yet now we part, and tears soak through my kerchief.
    Do not think it strange that I stand sorrowful before the wind—
    To meet a soul from home while far away is a rare and precious thing.
  footnotes:
    - Sanyang (山陽) refers to the region in Tang China where the poet likely encountered this fellow traveler from the Korean peninsula.
    - The image of tears soaking the kerchief serves as both a literal expression of grief and a classical symbol of the sorrow of separation and exile.
